 204:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c **** 
 205:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c **** /**
 206:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****    * @brief  Update SystemCoreClock variable according to Clock Register Values.
 207:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         The SystemCoreClock variable contains the core clock (HCLK), it can
 208:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         be used by the user application to setup the SysTick timer or configure
 209:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         other parameters.
 210:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           
 211:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @note   Each time the core clock (HCLK) changes, this function must be called
 212:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         to update SystemCoreClock variable value. Otherwise, any configuration
 213:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         based on this variable will be incorrect.         
 214:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *     
 215:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @note   - The system frequency computed by this function is not the real 
 216:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           frequency in the chip. It is calculated based on the predefined 
 217:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           constant and the selected clock source:
 218:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             
 219:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is HSI, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSI_VALUE(*)
 220:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                                              
 221:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is HSE, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSE_VALUE(**)
 222:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                          
 223:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is PLL, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSE_VALUE(**) 
 224:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             or HSI_VALUE(*) multiplied/divided by the PLL factors.
 225:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         
 226:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         (*) HSI_VALUE is a constant defined in stm32f4xx_hal_conf.h file (default value
 227:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             16 MHz) but the real value may vary depending on the variations
 228:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *             in voltage and temperature.   
 229:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *    
 230:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         (**) HSE_VALUE is a constant defined in stm32f4xx_hal_conf.h file (its value
 231:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *              depends on the application requirements), user has to ensure that HSE_VALUE
 232:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *              is same as the real frequency of the crystal used. Otherwise, this function
 233:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *              may have wrong result.
 234:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *                
 235:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *         - The result of this function could be not correct when using fractional
 236:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *           value for HSE crystal.
 237:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   *     
 238:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @param  None
 239:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   * @retval None
 240:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c ****   */
 241:../common/cmsis/device/system_stm32f4xx.c **** void SystemCoreClockUpdate(void)
